    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1253"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1253">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/392.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Refer to Department’s August 8 sent to Saltillo, regarding taxes imposed upon
                    American firms at Tampico by General Nafarrate. Have you brought this matter to
                    attention of General Carranza? If not do so at once, and insist that he
                    immediately telegraph General Nafarrate to withdraw his demands, as taxes appear
                    to be excessive and discriminatory, and if enforced will result in closing down
                    these firms.</p>
                <p>The Consul at Tampico has been instructed to advise American firms of
                    Department’s attitude regarding payment of these taxes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
